        "timestamp": "2020-12-17 13:36:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > not so sure about these changes we seem to loose a lot of details for when we want file-output. Would it be possible to have 2 different 'profiles' and make std-out/console the default?!\n> \n> yes, it is possible to have two different appenders. I will add the file appender back\n\nif we dont need the file appender, my suggestion is to not add it.",
